Text.Value: See, Phos? This'un has RESPEC'! Now, where was I...
I can buy m'own bloody drinks, thanks.
Don't... don't... don't even know what that means.

EditorData.NodeContext: Unconcerned by our threat, drunkenly trailing off.

Text.Value: Oh, you rancid bastard.
So Tut's gonna tell you what he knows about the Stone Lord, you're going to leave us to our merry old time, and you're not going to put my name near any of this - yes?

EditorData.NodeContext: Hushed, barely-restrained impatience - laying out the terms by which he'll help in return for us leaving

Text.Value: Back to sleep! Look, Tut here is an old friend of Nine-Fingers - saved her as a kid or some such, I don't know.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Gestures at Tut, focusing on us - dropping the drunk act and speaking in hushed tones.
EditorData.NodeContext: Gestures at Tut, focusing on us - dropping the drunk act and speaking in hushed tones.

Text.Value: Ugh! You're disgus- disgus-... You're a mess, mate.

EditorData.logicalname: Alias (POST-COUP - ZHENT WON (delete if NPC is Guild))

Text.Value: Wait. I want to hear about the Stone Lord. Let him finish.
Eh? Bugger off. I'm TALKIN' to my FRIEN' about an OOZE.

EditorData.logicalname: HASMET, DIDN'T GET STONE LORD HINT

Text.Value: *Belch.*
Don't care about Stone Lord, Tut. Don't care about some ambush. I asked - d'you eat my last pickled ooze?
That's my last one. Going home.

EditorData.logicalname: POST-COUP - ZHENT WON (delete if NPC is Guild)

Text.Value: See - see - Nine-Fingers is a master of stratergic - strateegil - she's clever, Phos.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Holding forth to his drinking buddy, absolutely pissed
EditorData.logicalname: PLAYER KNOWS ABOUT STONE LORD AMBUSH

Text.Value: I've been to fouler fest-halls than this. And you have the stage presence of a Volothamp Geddarm.

EditorData.NodeContext: Nonchalant - she doesn't rate this guy's acting skills

Text.Value: Leave them.
Hah?

EditorData.NodeContext: blearily, not fully there

Text.Value: *Belch.* See? Mine, s'fresh.
But... I've been buying.
Managed to keep out of the worst of the fighting. Now just need to keep from sobering up.

EditorData.logicalname: POST-COUP - ZHENT WON (delete if NPC is Guild)

Text.Value: Now - you were speaking to my friend. Politely.

EditorData.NodeContext: Returning to topic, but sweetly reminding the thug of her threat if he's rude again

Text.Value: Happy? Now - away wir ye. We wan' drink in peace.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Happy is pointed to us, dead sober - then resuming his drunk act and shoooing us away

Text.Value: Can't lie. It's a relief to have that old fart off my hands.
But if I don't keep him busy like she asked, he's likely to run off and try to take on the Stone Lord himself.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hushed, urgent - we're going to get him in trouble

Text.Value: TUT! Stone Lord.
Didn't eat it. S'one way to prove it, if you really wan' help.
No need f'such sauce, my friend. You're lucky I'm a happy drunk. Now - where was I?

EditorData.NodeContext: Drunkenly affronted, haughtily deigns to return to his story

Text.Value: I never... I never asked him to.

EditorData.NodeContext: Phos, a little panicked, wanting to clarify with us that he never asked to kiss Tut's arse.

Text.Value: Waste any more of my time, and I will turn you into a pickled ooze.
Hah! How y'like the smell of innocence? Bu' you're a good sport - so what was I sayin'?
*Belch.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Tut leans forward and belches in our face.

Text.Value: I'm just here to listen to his fine man's tale about the Stone Lord.
I've got a tab running at the bar. Indulge me and I'll keep it open, just for you.
Won't fight the Stone Lord out in th'open. But she's got a spot picked out, see, an'-
YEAH!
You. You are a very beautiful person.

EditorData.NodeContext: Utter sincerity. He'd adopt us if he could.

Text.Value: *As for the contents of your own stomach...*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player looks disgusted, and steps back from NPC

Text.Value: D'ya see? I killed ten of 'em, without even droppin' me mug.

EditorData.logicalname: POST-COUP - GUILD WON (delete if NPC is Zhent)

Text.Value: He's sleepin'.
Hoy. Phos? Seen Phos?

EditorData.NodeContext: drunk, squinting up at us - looking for his friend, but too drink to care that much

Text.Value: Nine-Fingers is gonna catch him with his claws in her coffers. I pity the bastard.

EditorData.NodeContext: Relish at the violent fate that awaits the Stone Lord.

Text.Value: Welcome t'the Guildhall! Faerûn's finest festhall, s'long as you're not sober.

EditorData.NodeContext: Turning to player with a welcoming nod

Text.Value: Stone Lord, aye! Bastard's going after the Counting House - but he doesn't know that that's just another Guild operation. Heh.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Jerking back to sudden consciousness as if he hadn't been falling asleep.
EditorData.NodeContext: Drunkenly finding a place in his story. Relish, slyly revealing that the Counting House is actually run by the criminal Guild

Text.Value: No, thank you.
You're sober - so why are you pretending you're not?
He's all riled up. Best you do g'way.

EditorData.NodeContext: Drunken tone, apologetic for his friend

EditorData.logicalname: Alias (POST-COUP - GUILD WON (delete if NPC is Zhent))

Text.Value: I'm sleepin'.
*Unlike his elder, the younger halfling - Phos - is stone cold sober. But for some reason, he's feigning drunkenness.*
The Counting House...? But what the hells could Minsc want there?
The Stone Lord. And swiftly, please - I can only hold my breath for so long.

EditorData.NodeContext: Repressed disgust. We were just assaulted with a vile but genial belch.

Text.Value: Ease off, eh mate? I don't even let Phos kiss me arse like that.

EditorData.NodeContext: He's drunk, but even he's embarrassed with how sycophantic the player is being.

Text.Value: *An assailing mist dampens your face - stale beer, garlic, and whatever else lurks in Tut's stomach.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player flinches from burp - using one of the NEGATIVE or HANDSUP_STOP reaction anims.

EditorData.logicalname: Alias (POST-COUP - ZHENT WON (delete if NPC is Guild))

Text.Value: Right, Tut. I think you've had enough.
Where was I?
Now, now - he who keeps his manners keeps his teeth, too. Besides, you are only pretending to be as wine-soaked as your friend here.

EditorData.NodeContext: Dry, hint of threat

Text.Value: G'WAY!
Why are you pretending to be drunk?
Or able to smell.

EditorData.NodeContext: Drunk, good-natured jeering

Text.Value: Heard it, one of Glitterbeard's lads tellin' tales! The Stone Lord got 'et by a mimic, and bust his way clean out!
I... ? How can you tell?

EditorData.NodeContext: Rumbled - he'd been pretending to be drunk and was about to dispute being called out, but switches to hushed tones instead - has no idea how he was spotted so easily

Text.Value: Let's settle the matter of the ooze first, then. It's clearly important.
Must you embarrass me in front of the city's lower life-forms?

EditorData.NodeContext: Muted disgust - we just puked while interrogating a Guild member that she had intimidated.

Synopsis: A lower city denizen visits the Guildhall for a drink with his friend. In truth, he's being fed drink by this sober friend to keep him out of trouble. But he knows where to listen, and has learned the location of the Stone Lord's ambush. We can learn it from him if we put up with his shit long enough.
